-- Vodafone’s Buchanan Set to Leave for ARM, Sunday Telegraph Says
-- B y   K e i t h   J e n k i n s
-- 2012-04-01T10:33:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-01/vodafone-s-buchanan-set-to-quit-for-arm-sunday-telegraph-says.html
Vodafone Group Plc (VOD)  Deputy Chairman
John Buchanan will resign from the world’s biggest mobile-phone
operator, the  Sunday Telegraph reported , without saying where it
got the information.  Buchanan will become chairman of  ARM Holdings Plc (ARM) , a
semiconductor design company that produces chip designs for much
of the world’s mobile-phone market, according to the newspaper.  A spokesman for Vodafone declined to comment when contacted
by Bloomberg News.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Keith Jenkins in London at 
